text.tspan: First, ultra-pure copper is electroformed
from commercial blanks. The mandrel is
removed and the copper is flattened and
machined to a smooth surface.
Smaller stock pieces are machined
from the large flat blank into many
sizes for the variety of parts needed.
Each stock piece is given a serial
number and tracked in the database.
Some pieces may need to leave the
mine and are exposed to cosmic rays.
Hollow Hex Rods, for example, need to
be paralene coated. The parts must not
travel by air to avoid saturating them
with cosmogenic isotopes.
When the parts are recieved they are stored
until needed for assembly. Each step in the
lifetime of the copper from mandrel to
assembled parts is tracked. All parts must
be cleaned according to collaboration
approved procedures.
